    <stitle>CAB: 7000 AND 8000 SERIES MODELS - REMOVAL AND INSTALLATION - Cab Cowl Tray</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1603809" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Cab Cowl Tray</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove both driver and passenger side windshield wiper arm and blade assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603802.xml" xrefid="x1603802">
                        <emph type="bold">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603802"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1603844" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1603844.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 62. Cab Cowl Tray</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WIPER PIVOT POST</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING STUDS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNTING NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WASHER HOSE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. CENTER MOUNTING BRACKET BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. EVAPORATOR BOX</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. COWL TRAY</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. RUBBER SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. ANTENNA</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove washer hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide rubber seal off antenna.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screw to evaporator box.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove center mounting bracket bolt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two mounting nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull the cowl tray off the mounting studs and wiper pivot posts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift cowl tray off the antenna and remove.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lower cowl tray over antenna and align with mounting studs and wiper pivot posts. (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two mounting nuts on the cowl tray (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62, Items 3 and 8</hotlnk>). Tighten nuts to 16 Lbf-ft (22 N&#8226;m),
                    DO NOT exceed 18 Lbf-ft (24 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install center mounting bracket bolt (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62, Item 5</hotlnk>). DO NOT overtighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install screw to evaporator box (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62, Items 6 and 7</hotlnk>). DO NOT overtighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide rubber seal down over antenna (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62, Items 9 and 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install washer hose (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1603844">Figure 62, Item 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install both driver and passenger side windshield wiper arm and blade assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16038_X1603802.xml" xrefid="x1603802">
                        <emph type="bold">WINDSHIELD WIPER ARM AND BLADE ASSEMBLY</emph>
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="x1603802"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn wipers on high speed, activate windshield washer, and check for proper wiper
                    operation. If required, adjust windshield wiper arm and blade assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
